dataset_description.json.Name: Abrupt hippocampal remapping signals resolution of memory interference.
Funding: This work was supported by NIH-NINDS R01 NS089729 awarded to B.A.K. and NIH-NEI K00EY031607 awarded to S.E.F.

README:
Associative memory task focus on resolving interferences between highly similar stimuli.

Related behavioral data and stimuli are on OSF: https://osf.io/vpq2x/

Exclusion criteria:
Sub 8 15 30 34 are excluded due to poor behavioral performance (learned pairmates <= 6 pairs by the 6th round)
Sub 16 is excluded due to movement (Max FD > 3.5mm).
